===Governors of Arkansas===
[[Image:AR Conway James Sevier.jpg|right|120px|thumb|[[James Sevier Conway]], first governor of Arkansas.]]
[[Image:Augustus Hill Garland - Brady-Handy.jpg|right|thumb|120px|[[Augustus Hill Garland]], 14th governor of Arkansas, and Attorney General of the United States.]]
[[Image:Sid mcmath1.JPG|right|thumb|120px|[[Sid McMath]], 42nd governor of Arkansas.]]
[[Image:B001057.jpg|right|thumb|120px|[[Dale Bumpers]], 46th governor of Arkansas.]]
[[Image:Bill Clinton.jpg|right|thumb|120px|[[Bill Clinton]], 50th and 52nd governor of Arkansas, and President of the United States.]]
[[Image:MDHuckabee.jpg|right|thumb|120px|[[Mike Huckabee]], 54th governor of Arkansas.]]
[[Image:MikeBeebeGovernorCropped.jpg|right|thumb|120px|[[Mike Beebe]], 55th and present governor of Arkansas.]]

The state of Arkansas was admitted to the union on [[June 15]] [[1836]].

{| class="wikitable"
!#!!Name!!Took office!!Left office!!Party!![[Lieutenant Governor of Arkansas|Lt. Governor]]<ref>The office of lieutenant governor was not created until 1914, and was not filled until 1926. The amendment to the state constitution creating the office was narrowly voted in by the electorate in 1914. The Speaker of the House declared that the measure had lost because it did not receive a majority of the highest vote total from that election. In 1925, it was discovered that a 1910 law amended this requirement such that only a majority of the votes on the specific question was required. Therefore, the 1914 initiative was declared to be valid.{{ref|ltgov|[K]}}</ref>!!Notes
